Here is the translation:

He will worship Hari with his heart's desire, and even a wolf will live at ease; 
Hari's devotee becomes a wolf himself, living as a slave in his own servitude.

The devotee is a wild elephant, worshipped by the Lord; 
The beautiful one, like clouds, has been taken away from me, Oh Rupaji; 
In this village, the devotee is as handsome.

Here is the translation:

The village remains quiet, Lord Swaminarayan's name is spoken; 
A devotee's life remains restless, worships God with tears.

Here is the translation:

Haribhakt che Premo Kulaal, Satangi ae Gam Jal;
Rudo Rabari Naam che Kal, Gam Goymaam Bhakt Bhalo.

Here are the translations:

Kanbee khushaal bechar naam, bai aval rahesano de gam;
Koli bhakt dayaali dhanoji, chaloji saaroji ne panoji.

Translated:
A foolish happy name is that of a young girl, who lives in some other village;
The God-fearing devotee has mercy, makes an offering, and then takes leave.

Here is the translation:

Himmatram ne jivnararam, Hareshwor ne Mahadev naam;
Kashiram Kubereji kahie, Gnanpatram naame dohi le.
